Sure! Here's a simple JavaScript program that reverses the words in a sentence:

```javascript
function reverseWords(sentence) {
    // Split the sentence into words
    var words = sentence.split(' ');

    // Reverse the array of words
    var reversedWords = words.reverse();

    // Join the reversed words back into a sentence
    var reversedSentence = reversedWords.join(' ');

    return reversedSentence;
}

// Example usage:
var input = "Hello world, this is a test.";
var output = reverseWords(input);
console.log(output);  // Outputs: "test. a is this world, Hello"
```

This function works by splitting the input sentence into an array of words using the space character as a delimiter. It then reverses the array of words and joins them back into a sentence with spaces. This effectively reverses the order of the words in the sentence.

